            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-2413] ContainerManager doesn&apos;t close the Timer it creates when stop() is called</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-2413</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ContainerManager creates a Timer object. It&apos;s stop() method cancel&apos;s the running task but doesn&apos;t close the Timer itself. This ends up leaking a Thread (internal to the Timer).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
